title: Critics: 'Jem' is anything but excitement - Click Orlando
text:
The new film, based on the pastel-colored '80s animated series about rock singer Jem -- a.k.a. Starlight Music mogul Jerrica Benton -- her band the Holograms and their battles with other groups, has allowed critics to sharpen up their knives. The movie "seems to be merely tossing ideas into the pot that it thinks might appeal to 9-year-olds," says New York Times critic Neil Genzlinger.
 Click Orlando.
